adors-tallest-waterfall|title=The Disappearance of Ecuador\u2019s Tallest Waterfall|date=2020-03-27|website=earthobservatory.nasa.gov|language=en|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n| <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.worldwaterfalldatabase.com/waterfall/San-Rafael-Cascada-de-373|title=San Rafael, Cascada de, Ecuador \u2013 World Waterfall Database|website=www.worldwaterfalldatabase.com|language=en|access-date=2020-01-17}}</ref>\n|-\n! 22\n| [[Urri\u00f0afoss]]\n| [[File:Urri\u00f0afoss2009.jpg|100px]]\n| {{sort|00360|360}}\n| 4\n| 229\n| [[\u00dej\u00f3rs\u00e1]]\n| {{flag|Iceland}}\n| {{coord|63.92506|-20.672678|format=dms|name=Urri\u00f0afoss}}\n| \n| <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.worldwaterfalldatabase.com/waterfall/Urrithafoss-14805|title=Urri\u00f0afoss, Iceland \u2013 World Waterfall Database|website=www.worldwaterfalldatabase.com|language=en|access-date=2020-01-17}}</ref>\n|-\n! 23\n| [[Augrabies Falls]]\n| [[File:Augrabie, Waterfalls, South Africa.jpg|100px]]\n| {{sort|00313|313}}\n| 56\n| 24\n| [[Orange River|Orange]]\n| {{flag|South Africa}}\n| {{coord|-28.591389|20.340296|format=dms|name=Augrabies Falls}}\n| \n| <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.worldwaterfalldatabase.com/waterfall/Augrabies-Falls-116|title=Augrabies Falls, South Africa \u2013 World Waterfall Database|website=www.worldwaterfalldatabase.com|language=en|access-date=2020-01-17}}</ref>\n|-\n! 24\n| [[Murchison Falls]]\n| [[File:Murchison Falls, Uganda (23475021234).jpg|100px]]\n| {{sort|00300|300}}\n| 43\n| 15\n| [[White Nile]]\n| {{flag|Uganda}}\n| {{coord|2.2785|31.6858|format=dms|name=Murchison Falls}}\n| \n| <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.worldwaterfalldatabase.com/waterfall/Murchison-Falls-121|title=Murchison Falls, Uganda \u2013 World Waterfall Database|website=www.worldwaterfalldatabase.com|language=en|access-date=2020-01-17}}</ref>\n|-\n! 25\n| [[Alexandra Falls]]\n| [[File:Alexandra Falls Hay River.jpg|100px]]\n| {{sort|00282|282}}\n| 32\n| 117\n| [[Hay River (Canada)|Hay River]]\n| {{flag|Canada}}\n| {{coord|60.5006|-116.2794|format=dms|name=Alexandra Falls}}\n| \n| <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.worldwaterfalldatabase.com/waterfall/Alexandra-Falls-19121|title=Alexandra Falls, Northwest Territories, Canada \u2013 World Waterfall Database|website=www.worldwaterfalldatabase.com|language=en|access-date=2020-01-17}}</ref>\n|-\n! 25\n| [[Louise Falls]]\n| [[File:Louise Falls Hay River.jpg|100px]]\n| {{sort|00282|282}}\n| 15\n| 183\n| [[Hay River (Canada)|Hay River]]\n| {{flag|Canada}}\n| {{coord|60.5033|-116.2414|format=dms|name=Louise Falls}}\n| \n| <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.worldwaterfalldatabase.com/waterfall/Louise-Falls-19168|title=Louise Falls, Northwest Territories, Canada \u2013 World Waterfall Database|website=www.worldwaterfalldatabase.com|language=en|access-date=2020-01-17}}</ref>\n|-\n! 27\n| [[Dettifoss]]\n| [[File:Dettifoss TimBekaert.JPG|100px]]\n| {{sort|00269|269}}\n| 51\n| 171\n| [[J\u00f6kuls\u00e1 \u00e1 Fj\u00f6llum]]\n| {{flag|Iceland}}\n| {{coord|65.8146330|-16.3843220|format=dms|name=Dettifoss}}\n| \n| <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.worldwaterfalldatabase.com/waterfall/Dettifoss-119|title=Dettifoss, Iceland \u2013 World Waterfall Database|website=www.worldwaterfalldatabase.com|language=en|access-date=2020-01-17}}</ref>\n|-\n! 27\n| [[Hafragilsfoss]]\n| [[File:Hafragilsfoss-2006-burras.de.jpg|100px]]\n| {{sort|00269|269}}\n| 27\n| 85\n| [[J\u00f6kuls\u00e1 \u00e1 Fj\u00f6llum]]\n| {{flag|Iceland}}\n| {{coord|65.8322810|-16.3991539|format=dms|name=Hafragilsfoss}}\n| \n| <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.worldwaterfalldatabase.com/waterfall/Hafragilsfoss-658|title=Hafragilsfoss, Iceland \u2013 World Waterfall Database|website=www.worldwaterfalldatabase.com|language=en|access-date=2020-01-17}}</ref>\n|-\n! 27\n| [[Selfoss (waterfall)|Selfoss]]\n| [[File:IJsland Selfoss woaterval.jpg|100px]]\n| {{sort|00269|269}}\n| 13\n| 387\n| [[J\u00f6kuls\u00e1 \u00e1 Fj\u00f6llum]]\n| {{flag|Iceland}}\n| {{coord|65.80495|-16.38657|format=dms|name=Selfoss}}\n| \n| <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.worldwaterfalldatabase.com/waterfall/Selfoss-659|title=Selfoss, Iceland \u2013 World Waterfall Database|website=www.worldwaterfalldatabase.com|language=en|access-date=2020-01-17}}</ref>\n|-\n! 27\n| [[R\u00e9ttarfoss]]\n| [[File:Aerial View of R\u00e9ttarfoss 21.05.2008 15-49-46.JPG|100px]]\n| {{sort|00269|269}}\n| ?\n| ?\n| [[J\u00f6kuls\u00e1 \u00e1 Fj\u00f6llum]]\n| {{flag|Iceland}}\n| {{coord|65.879645|-16.435802|format=dms|name=R\u00e9ttarfoss}}\n| \n| <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.worldwaterfalldatabase.com/waterfall/Rettarfoss-14669|title=R\u00e9ttarfoss, Iceland \u2013 World Waterfall Database|website=www.worldwaterfalldatabase.com|language=en|access-date=2020-01-17}}</ref>\n|}\n\nThe first five waterfalls by power (Gua\u00edra, Khone Phapheng, Iguaz\u00fa, Niagara, and Victoria) are called the ''Great Five Waterfalls''.<ref>\u0413. \u0422. \u0410\u0440\u0441\u0435\u0435\u0432. \u0412\u043e\u0434\u043e\u043f\u0430\u0434\u044b. \u2014 \u041c.: \u041c\u044b\u0441\u043b\u044c, 1987. \u2014 \u0421. 14. \u2014 127 \u0441.</ref><ref>\u0412. \u0418. \u0417\u0430\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0436\u043d\u044b\u0439, \u041a. \u0412. \u0417\u0432\u043e\u0440\u044b\u043a\u0438\u043d. \u041c\u0435\u0442\u043e\u0434\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0433\u0438\u044f \u0438 \u0440\u0435\u0433\u0438\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u0444\u0438\u0437\u0438\u043a\u043e-\u0433\u0435\u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0444\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0435 \u0438\u0441\u0441\u043b\u0435\u0434\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0438\u044f. \u2014 \u041c.: \u0413\u0435\u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0444\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0435 \u043e\u0431\u0449\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e \u0421\u0421\u0421\u0420, 1975. \u2014 \u0421. 60. \u2014 78 \u0441.</ref>\n\n==Prehistoric waterfalls==\n{{see also|Outburst flood}}\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Waterfall!!Maximum daily flow rate (m<sup>3</sup>/s)!!Tallest single drop (m) !! Widt